<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="855" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12704.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.].</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The peace delegates came to this Consulate early this morning and
                            awakened me. They felt sore and discouraged at the treatment shown them
                            by Constitutionalist officials since their arrival in Tampico. They had
                            decided to quit and wanted me to accompany them to Texas. It was only by
                            the strongest appeals to their patriotism and the advantages of peace
                            that this Consulate induced them to continue on to the conference. We
                            did this because we knew how greatly our President and the Department
                            desired bringing the two parties together. We hope our action pleases
                            you.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>